snippet.textDisplay:
To the very beautiful Elsy💖,
Congratulations first and foremost to you, yours, and everyone in your familiá that is so excited for you both on sharing this amazing journey called life God has granted us all.
Due to evil and its influencers, people of God must remain faithful and steadfast.
You are one of God's people, so never fear... I don't have any type of social media and I haven't had it for years. Mind you, this is coming from someone who was extremely "worldly" at one point.
I've never even commented on a YouTube page before, but as I was getting ready to turn on some sleeping music, I noticed your video and I felt so compelled to write you.
I want you to be at peace and as you do, to continue to pray... Love, appreciate, and enjoy every single moment and process of being a mommy now. It's so miraculous and a true gift from God.
It's okay to do what is right for you and you're little one in order to heal and to be at peace, whatever that might mean. You certainly will feel so many emotions along the way and that is completely wonderful and normal. Continue to not allow harmful effects/psychological warfare contribute to the positive and necessary development/growth of baby during stressful moments. Plus, messes make memories! So, enjoy those little moments as well💞.
Allow yourself to find peace and clarity. And some of the best advice my mother ever gave me was, "Never make permanent decisions based on temporary emotions". This is so important. Allow God to drive your actions and not the ugliness inside of others.
I don't know you personally, but, you did move me today in a way that my heart hurt with yours and I just wanted to reach out and let you know that you are beautiful inside and out!
I appreciate you choosing to be a soul on this earth that chooses Love💗 over Hate💔.
We need more love. We need better. Thank you and may God continue to bless you all.

snippet.textDisplay:
) In May 2019, members of the Minnesota House of Representatives and the Minnesota Senate sent official letters to the Minnesota Medical Association (MMA) expressing concern over forced organ harvesting in China.

The letters from the House of Representatives and the Minnesota Senate, written by Representative Nels Pierson (R-Stewartville) and Senator Jim Abeler (R-Anoka), were supported by 77 House and Senate co-signers, two of whom are practicing physicians. Both letters expressed concern over Minnesota residents obtaining unethically sourced organs from countries such as China and also mentioned concern over, “…Chinese medical personnel who are trained in Minnesota that may assist in forced organ harvesting.”

The MMA is a non-profit professional association that represents Minnesota physicians, residents, and medical students.

From a Minnesota government press release:

“We need a plan and guideline to prevent anyone from profiting from this horrendous practice in China,” said Sen. Abeler (R-Anoka). “It is vital that we continue to condemn forced harvesting and discourage our citizens from taking advantage of this crime against humanity. Senator Carolyn Laine (DFL-Columbia Heights) declared, “This is a serious human rights issue and we all need to take a vocal stand on this practice.”
